In England, in the seven days to 06 March, there were 222,852 new confirmed cases (394.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 27 February, there were 167,532 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 33% (55,320 extra cases). The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 11 March is 16,481,364 (29,144.7 cases per 100,000 population).
